tic\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528909\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 16, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jju1665702976982.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jju1665702976982.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jju1665702976982.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jju1665702976982\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Unsupported DBMS Storage Formats\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">It is possible that your DBMS supports a storage format that is not covered by a Uniface connector-level packing code.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"jju1665702976982__p_d62123e1_d62124e1_d62125e1\">Depending on the extent of the incompatibility, this can be solved by:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jju1665702976982__li_d27176e1_d27177e1_d27178e1\">Recognizing this limitation and never using that DBMS storage format. This is the only solution if Uniface has no data type that corresponds to the storage format in the DBMS, and no packing code that provides the data in a format that you could convert to match the DBMS storage format.\n <p class=\"p\" id=\"jju1665702976982__p_d62126e1_d62127e1_d62128e1\">This can be the case when the DBMS storage format is so exotic that there is no remotely similar Uniface packing code. By not supporting a DBMS storage format in your connector, you do not limit the Uniface functionality. However, the connector will not be able to access fields in the database with an unsupported storage format.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jju1665702976982__li_d27179e1_d27180e1_d27181e1\">Carrying out the required data conversion in the connector itself. If the unsupported DBMS storage format is similar to one of the Uniface packing codes, you can choose that packing code and make sure that the connector handles the required format conversions in the data manipulation connector requests.\n <div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"jju1665702976982__note_w3955ab1b5b3b3b1_w3956ab1b5b3b3_w3957ab1b5b3_w3958ab1b5_w3959ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> This is an extremely complicated approach; there are no connector service functions available to help you carry out the conversion, so be warned that this solution is your responsibility.</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eed1665702975775.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Database Connector Interface</a><p>The Database Connector Interface is an API for building custom database connectors.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528909\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528909\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Unsupported DBMS Storage Formats Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 16, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Unsupported DBMS Storage Formats It is possible that your DBMS supports a storage format that is not covered by a Uniface connector-level packing code. Depending on the extent of the incompatibility, this can be solved by: Recognizing this limitation and never using that DBMS storage format. This is the only solution if Uniface has no data type that corresponds to the storage format in the DBMS, and no packing code that provides the data in a format that you could convert to match the DBMS storage format. This can be the case when the DBMS storage format is so exotic that there is no remotely similar Uniface packing code. By not supporting a DBMS storage format in your connector, you do not limit the Uniface functionality. However, the connector will not be able to access fields in the database with an unsupported storage format. Carrying out the required data conversion in the connector itself. If the unsupported DBMS storage format is similar to one of the Uniface packing codes, you can choose that packing code and make sure that the connector handles the required format conversions in the data manipulation connector requests. CAUTION: This is an extremely complicated approach; there are no connector service functions available to help you carry out the conversion, so be warned that this solution is your responsibility. Related Links Database Connector Interface The Database Connector Interface is an API for building custom database connectors. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}